[Black "A dubious move order to avoid the Maroczy Bind #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5
{ Kicking Black's knight and forcing it to go home again. } 7... Nh5
{ The best attempt for Black. } 8. Bc4 d5 9. exd6 Qxd6
{ After this move, our structure will be better in the long run.   Si  9...exd6  10.O-O  Black is not ready yet to open the position like this. }
10. Qf3 Be6 11. Bb3
{ We will follow with moves such as O-O and Ne4. Our bishop is so great on b3 as it creates a favorable tension between the light-squared bishops. If Black takes on b3 the a-file will be open and will facilitate White's pressure against the a7-pawn. }
