1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Nxc6 dxc6
{ This move allows us to into a better endgame thanks to our development advantage. }
7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. Bc4
{ It is important to exert a quick pressure on f7 to gain more tempi in development. If BLack plays ...e5 under good circumstances, Black will be closer to equality. }
8... Ke8 9. e5
{ Changing our structure into a better one for us in the long run.   9.a4  . }
9... Nd7 10. e6 fxe6 11. Bxe6 Bg7 12. Be3
{ We will finish ouir development by castling. The fact that e4 will be a nice square for our knight and that Black has a permanent weakness on e7 will guarantee us a comfortable advantage. }
