11. e5 Nd5
{ 11...Ng8  12.Bg2  black cannot afford to delay their development any further. }
12. Nxd5 exd5 13. Bg2
{ White will get the pawn back with a nice development advantage and, above all, an excellent piece placement putting pressure on the b7 and f7-squares. }
13... Be7
{ 13...d6  14.Qe2  Black cannot afford to open the position which such a poor piece development. }
14. Bxd5 { 14.Qf3  . } 14... d6 15. exd6 Qxd6 16. Qf3 O-O 17. O-O-O
{ White has a huge advantage thanks to the fact that we seize the center and that we put pressure on BLack's weaknesses. }
