{ After this move, we will enter in a forced sequence that will lead to a favorable endgame for us.   14...Bxd4  15.Qxd4  . }
15. e6 Bxd4 16. exf7+ Rxf7 17. Qxd4
{ This move achieves the goal of ruining Black's pawn structure. } 17... d6
{ Necessary move to be able to develop the bishop.   17...Re7+  18.Kd2  Our king cannot be attacked and we will hide it on c1 if necessary. However, BLack's king will suffer because of the weaknesses on the light squares and also due to the fact that our rooks will quickly get to the open files. }
18. Bxd5 { Getting the pawn back and creating a very annoying pin. } 18... Be6
19. O-O-O Bxd5 20. Qxd5
{ The weaknesses on the 7th rank plus Black's weakened pawn structure turns this endgame into a complete hell for the second player. }
*

