10... Nf6
{ A very human move. Black is afraid of the fact that the knight could end up trapped on g8 after we play g5.   10...e5  11.g5  . }
11. g5 Nd7 12. Qg3
{ After this precise continuation we put Black in a lot of trouble. In case of exchanging on g3, we reach a very favorable endgame -as the g5 pawn converts h7 in a permanent weakness- and, in case Black removes the queen,we gain an excellent square for our queen and besides, we have the chance to continue with f4. }
