{ The pawn on h5 is extremely annoying for Black. If it gets to h6, Black's king will be very weak and, if they play ...h6 themselves, they will create a hook on g5 for us to exploit in the future.   Our plan is very straightforward: developing the bishops to d3 -to support e4- and to d2 -as prophylacis against ...b4. We will preferably bring the queen to g3, but on e2 is also OK. }
9... h6 10. Bd3 { Going for our standard setup. } 10... Bb7 11. Qg4
{ 11.Qf3  . } 11... Nf6 12. Qg3
{ And now we can take our time to develop, while Black will struggle to do the same. }
