10... e5
{ Weakening the light squares too much and this will be more noticeable once our pawn reaches g5.   10...d6?!  this move does not fight for the center, so it makes little sense. We can continue with our main plan naturally and we get an advantage.  11.f3  . }
11. f3 d5 { 11...Bc5  12.g4  . } 12. g4 Be6
{ 12...dxe4  13.g5  .   12...d4  13.Na4  this structure is usually advantageous for White; we will calmly prepare c3 with a great endgame. }
13. Bd2
{ And we have more moves to improve our position, waiting for them to create more weaknesses. }
