10... d5
{ The most logical -and the best!- move. Maybe this is the move that we will most likely face over the board. }
11. Bd3
{ Developing the bishop to its most natural square and controlling the center. Besides, we are starting to exert pressure on h7. }
11... Be7 12. f3 Rb8
{ A very logical move to hinder the development of our Bc1. Now we have two possible plans: the usual one -play for g4, develop and improving our position little by little- or play much more concretely. }
13. b4
{ A very concrete -and risky- move. If Black is not careful, we will control very well the dark squares and some extra space.   13.g4!?  is much more solid  13...Bd6  14.Rb1  we keep controlling the board and improving our position little by little. }
