13. Be3 a5
{ Intending to play ...Ba6 to trade the c8-bishop, which is one of the worst black pieces. }
14. Na4
{ Another interesting idea as a concept for this or any other position. We can simply leave the bishop on d3 and recapture with the c-pawn. After the trade, we can put pressure on that file. }
14... Ba6 15. g4
{ Dominating the whole board. If Black takes on d3. Black will open the c-file for us, which we will use to put pressure on c6. }
15... Bxd3 16. cxd3
{ We will bring our rook to c1 next and Black's c6-pawn will suffer. Our bishop and knight have a tight control of the c5-square. }
*

