[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3) Anti-Taimanov Move Order"]
[Black "5...Qb6 6.Nb5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. a3
{ When I discovered this move, I could not resist recommending it. It is designed specifically against Taimanov players @@StartBracket@@the best continuation here is ...Nf6 and, after Nc3, we will transpose directly to the Two Knights with a3@@@EndBracket@@. However, most Taimanov players will have no idea of that position and will try to transpose to what they know with ...Qc7, after which they will get a nasty surprise. }
5... Qb6 6. Nb5
{ Aiming to control the dark squares on the opponent's camp, as they cannot play ...d6. }
6... Bc5 { 6...Nf6  7.N1c3  Bc5  8.Qd2  is the same thing. } 7. Qd2
{ Defending f2 and threats such as Nd6 or even b4+Bb2 are still in the air. }
7... Nf6
{ 7...a6?!  does nothing to stop our threat:  8.Nd6+  Bxd6  9.Qxd6  we have the bishop pair and, above all, we control the dark squares.   Si  8...Ke7  9.Nc4  Qa7  10.b4  with a total control of the dark squares and, besides, Black's king is in the middle of the board. }
8. N1c3 { Defending e4 and threatening Na4. } 8... Ng4
{ The most concrete move.   8...O-O  9.Na4  .   8...a6  9.Nd6+  Bxd6  10.Qxd6  and we control the dark squares for free. }
9. Qg5 { Sacrificing the f2-pawn in return for a quick counterplay. } 9...
Bxf2+ { 9...Nxf2??  10.Qxg7  Rf8  11.Na4  . } 10. Kd1
{ A strange position. Our king is very safe on d1, as it is surrounded by our pieces, so we will enter on g7 and we have a knight ready to jump to d6. }
10... Nce5 11. Qxg7 Ng6
{ A necessary move to clear the e5-square for the g4-knight. Besides, it defends the rook without having to move it to f8. }
12. h3 N4e5 13. Qf6 { Na4 and Nd5 are real threats now. } 13... Bh4
{ 13...a6  14.Nd5  .   13...Bc5  14.Na4  . } 14. Nd5
{ This move decides the game because Wite wins material. } 14... Bxf6
{ 14...exd5  15.Nd6+  Kf8  16.Bh6+  Mate! } 15. Nxb6 axb6 16. Nc7+
{ Winning material. The knight can safely get out of the corner. } *

