[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3) Anti-Taimanov Move Order"]
[Black "5...Bc5 6.Nb3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. a3
{ When I discovered this move, I could not resist recommending it. It is designed specifically against Taimanov players @@StartBracket@@the best continuation here is ...Nf6 and, after Nc3, we will transpose directly to the Two Knights with a3@@@EndBracket@@. However, most Taimanov players will have no idea of that position and will try to transpose to what they know with ...Qc7, after which they will get a nasty surprise. }
5... Bc5
{ This is one of the best moves for Black here. However, I find it difficult to play if we don't know it because Black's setup is far away from the familiar ones. }
6. Nb3 { Winning a tempo and continuing our development. } 6... Be7
{ This move make some sense. } 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. f4
{ Very concrete move. As usual, we want to force Black to play ...d6 to remove the flexibility of going ...d5 in one move and, in addition, the f3-square is better secured. }
8... O-O
{ 8...d6  as usual, this is a concession, as it loses the flexibility of going ...d5 and this strengthens our g4 ideas.  9.Be3  . }
9. Be3 d5
{ 9...d6  10.g4  intending to follow up with g5 to continue the attack. } 10.
e5 Ne8
{ This interesting retreat is also the most precise. Black wants to play ...f6.   10...Nd7  11.Bd3  leaves Black in an inferior version of a French defense, and White will play Qh5 and force Black to create hooks that will allow White's pawns to open the position later on. }
11. Qd3
{ A weird -but concrete- move. Frome here, the queen will not be hit by possible ...Nc4 jumps and, besides, it will not run into a possible pin after ...a6+...b5+...b4 from Black. White also gets ready to castle queenside. }
11... f6 12. exf6 Nxf6
{ 12...Bxf6  13.O-O-O  Nd6  14.Kb1  following with g3 next to develop the light-squared bishop. }
13. O-O-O a6
{ 13...Bd7  14.g3  finishing our development and exerting pressure on e6. } 14.
g3 b5 15. Nd4
{ Again, bringing our pieces to attack the e6-pawn. Besides, we have a very healthy pawn structure. }
*

