{ We want to force Black to go ...d6 to be able to develop our queen to f3 without being in the way. }
8... d6 9. Qf3 e5
{ THe only -and the best- move that does not transpose to those lines already seen via the other move order.   9...Qc7  10.O-O-O  .   9...O-O  10.O-O-O  Qc7  . }
10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. h3
{ Preventing both ...Bg4 and ...Ng4 and we can give rise to O-O-O. } 11... Rb8
{ 11...O-O  12.O-O-O  Qc7  13.g4  with good counterplay.   After  11...exf4  12.Bxf4  the d6-pawn suffers after O-O-O. }
