{ 10...O-O  11.Bg5  followed by f4 with a nice attack. } 11. Bxa7 Rxa7 12. g4
{ Starting our expansion. Apart from the fact that we gain some space with this move, it works as a prophylaxis against Black's plan with ...b4+...Bd7 as after g5 Black's knight will run of squares to go to. }
12... b4 13. Na4
{ A correct move only if Black's plan with ...Bd7 is not fast enough. } 13...
O-O { 13...Bd7?!  14.g5  . } 14. g5 Ne8 15. Qe3
{ Preparing our expansion on the kingside.   15.f4?!  e5  we are not ready to go f5 as the g5-pawn would be hanging. }
