14. Na4 Bd7
{ If  14...e5  15.g5  Ne8  16.Qe3  , giving the b6-square to the knight and going for the kingside expansion or simply for doubling our rooks on the d-file. }
15. g5 Ne8 16. Qe3
{ We will follow with f4 with a nice position. In case of e5, the d5-square will be free for us to use it with our knight going there via b6. }
