7. Rg1
{ Defending quickly the g4-pawn to prevent tactical tricks and preparing an eventual break on g5. This rook move is also useful in some lines, where White can play Bg2 after Black's pawn break on d5 and the subsequent trades. }
7... Nc6 { 7...Be7  8.Be3  Nc6  . } 8. Be3 a6
