11... e5 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. g5 hxg5 14. hxg5 d4 15. gxf6 gxf6 16. O-O-O Be6 17.
Rg3
{ With the idea of retreating the bishop to take on c3 with the rook and put pressure on the c-file }
17... Qc7 18. Bd2 dxc3 19. Rxc3
{ White is exerting a nice pressure on the queenside. Kb1 comes next to regroup our pieces. }
