1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4
{ In this chapter we will have a look at some Black sidelines that BLack has at their disposal in this position. Objectively, they are not dangerous for us, but it is important to know them because they contain some hidden traps. }
4... Bc5 { Hoping for tactical tricks along the a7-g1 diagonal. } 5. Be3
{ Developing and reinforcing the a7-g1 diagonal. } 5... Qb6
{ Attacking b2 and adding another piece to put pressure on the diagonal.   5...Nf6!?  6.Nc3  Bb4  7.e5  Nd5  8.Bd2  . }
6. Na3
{ From this square, the knight can have access to very useful squares such as c4 or b5. }
6... d5
{ If  6...Qxb2?  the queen gets trapped.  7.Nab5!  Nf6  8.a3  Nxe4  9.Rb1  Qa2  10.Qc1  Na6  11.Nb3  the queen cannot get out.   If  7...Na6  8.a3!  d5  9.Rb1  Qa2  10.Rb3  followed by Nc3. }
