6. e5 Ne4 { The most direct move, preventing the Bd2 line, but... } 7. Qg4 Nxc3
8. Qxg7 Rf8 { 8...Ne4+  9.c3  . } 9. a3
{ The bishop has to decide whether to defend the knight or the rook. } 9...
Nb5+ 10. axb4 Nxd4 11. Bg5
{ This move is key to take away the e7-square from the queen. } 11... Nxc2+ 12.
Kd1 Qxg5 { 12...Qb6  13.Kxc2  followed by Bh6. } 13. Qxg5 Nxa1 14. b5
{ Qc1 comes next, finishing off the game. } 14... Nb3 15. Qe3 Na5 16. Qc3
{ We take on c8 or on a5. Black can resign. } *

