1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4
{ In this chapter we will have a look at some Black sidelines that BLack has at their disposal in this position. Objectively, they are not dangerous for us, but it is important to know them because they contain some hidden traps. }
4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4
{ The so called Pin Variation of the Sicilian, a line that Jobava has played quite a lot recently.  You have to be careful and prepared to play some strange positions.   5...Bc5  6.e5  Qb6  . }
6. e5 Nd5 7. Bd2 { Forcing Black to make a decision. } 7... Bxc3 8. bxc3 O-O
{ This move has been tried by Jobava many times. It is not easy to find the best line for White and this is what makes this line so interesting. However, once we know it, this line is rather dubious. }
9. c4 { Kicking the knight away to a more passive square. } 9... Ne7 10. Nb5
{ The key move and usually the one that people do not know about. It is key to prevent ...d6 in order to hinder BLack's development. }
10... Nbc6 11. Bc3 a6 12. Nd6 Nxe5 { Do we lose a pawn?   12...Ng6  13.h4  . }
13. f4 N5c6 14. Qh5 { Followed by O-O-O with a devastating attack. } *

