[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6
{ After this move we enter directly in the Accelerated Dragon. In return of giving up the center, Black will have a solid control of the central dark squares. }
5. c4
{ Going into a Maroczy Bind structure. White gains space in the center and takes advantage of it. We have to be a bit careful on the next moves, as Black may have some tactical tricks at their disposal. }
5... Bg7 6. Be3
{ It is important to not take on c6 because this will help Black's development. Although the b2-pawn is hanging -which can be scary-, Black has no way of exploiting it. }
6... Qb6
{ This move has become quite fashionable recently. Black aims to un-coordinate the white pieces. }
7. Nb3 Qd8 8. Qd2
{ This ensures that we do not have doubled pawns on the c-file. } 8... Nf6
{ 8...d6  9.Nc3  . } 9. Nc3
{ We continue our development calmly, ...Ng4 is not troublesome. } 9... Ng4
{ 9...d6  10.Be2  O-O  11.O-O  . } 10. Bf4
{ It is so important to not allow Black to take our bishop in exchange for a knight as this will make the g7-bishop become a monster. Now the knight does nothing on g4. }
10... d6 11. h3 Nf6 12. Be2
{ Followed by O-O, completing our development with a comfortable position. } *

