1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6
{ After this move we enter directly in the Accelerated Dragon. In return of giving up the center, Black will have a solid control of the central dark squares. }
5. c4
{ Going into a Maroczy Bind structure. White gains space in the center and takes advantage of it. We have to be a bit careful on the next moves, as Black may have some tactical tricks at their disposal. }
5... Bg7 6. Be3
{ It is important to not take on c6 because this will help Black's development. Although the b2-pawn is hanging -which can be scary-, Black has no way of exploiting it. }
6... Nf6 7. Nc3 O-O
{ If  7...Qa5  threatening the Nxe4 cheapo  8.Nb3  Qd8  9.Be2  we gain extra tempi that we will use by playing O-O Qd2 and bringing ur rooks to the center.   No @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/q7/2PNP3/2N1B3/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 5 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Qd2?  Nxe4  9.Nxe4  Qxd2+  10.Bxd2  Nxd4  . }
8. Be2 b6
{ Practically nobody plays with the bishop on b7 anymore. The pawn on b6 takes many squares away from the queen on d8 and, once we place a pawn on f3, the bishop will be blocked. }
9. Qd2 Bb7 10. f3 Rc8
{ 10...Qb8  11.O-O-O  followed by Kb1 and the h-pawn push. Black's setup with the bishop on b7 only hinders Black's development. }
11. O-O Nh5 12. Ndb5
{ The knight is incredibly annoying on b5, but kicking it back with a6 is not a good option due to the fact that b6 will be permanently weak. }
12... a6 13. Na3
{ And the knight will return to the game via vía c2, while the b6-pawn will be weak forever. }
