[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6
{ After this move we enter directly in the Accelerated Dragon. In return of giving up the center, Black will have a solid control of the central dark squares. }
5. c4
{ Going into a Maroczy Bind structure. White gains space in the center and takes advantage of it. We have to be a bit careful on the next moves, as Black may have some tactical tricks at their disposal. }
5... Bg7 6. Be3
{ It is important to not take on c6 because this will help Black's development. Although the b2-pawn is hanging -which can be scary-, Black has no way of exploiting it. }
6... Nf6 7. Nc3 O-O
{ If  7...Qa5  threatening the Nxe4 cheapo  8.Nb3  Qd8  9.Be2  we gain extra tempi that we will use by playing O-O Qd2 and bringing ur rooks to the center.   No @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/q7/2PNP3/2N1B3/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 5 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Qd2?  Nxe4  9.Nxe4  Qxd2+  10.Bxd2  Nxd4  . }
8. Be2 d6 9. O-O Bd7 10. Re1
{ A very interesting idea that has hardly been tested. We bring the rook to the e-file quickly @@StartBracket@@considering that our plan is based on Nd5 and recapturing with the e-pawn in the future, this makes a lot of sense.@@EndBracket@@. }
10... Nxd4
{ 10...Rc8  11.h3  controlling the knight jumps to g4 to continue with Qd2 with a nice central domination. }
11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. Qc2 { CFinishing our development and defending the pawn. }
12... a5
{ 12...Nd7  is one of the most typical ideas. We will get the same type of position as in the main line.  13.Bxg7  Kxg7  14.Bf1  clearing the e-file for the rook to put pressure on after Nd5, as we will recapture with the e-pawn.   12...Qc7  13.Bf1  clearing the e-file and we keep on preparing plans like b4 or Nd5. }
13. b3
{ This way we can reply with b4 to ...a4 preventing Black from taking en passant. }
13... Nd7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Rad1
{ After this, our position will be very comfy. Black has hardly any counterplay or pawn breaks because we have all of them under tight control @@StartBracket@@...a4 is met by b4, ...b5 is so well defended and ...f5 would be horrible due to the weakness it leaves behind@@EndBracket@@. We are also going to take advantage of the fact that that BLack's knight has gone far away from its king to create more weaknesses on Black's castling with h4+h5. }
15... Nc5 16. e5 { Blowing Black's pawn structure up. } 16... Qb6 17. exd6 exd6
18. Bf1
{ 1-0 @@StartBracket@@73@@EndBracket@@ Tylecek,D @@StartBracket@@2167@@EndBracket@@-Sciarretta,R @@StartBracket@@2176@@EndBracket@@ LSS email 2018 Black has a very serious weakness on d6 while our whole position is fully harmonious. Taking immediately on d6 is perfectly possible -and human-, but the fact that the text move was chosen in a correspondence game says everything we have to know about this position. }
