[Round "?"]
[White "10) A dubious move order to avoid the Maroczy Bind"]
[Black "6...dxc6 7.Qxd8+ #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Nxc6 dxc6
{ This move allows us to into a better endgame thanks to our development advantage. }
7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. Bc4
{ It is important to exert a quick pressure on f7 to gain more tempi in development. If BLack plays ...e5 under good circumstances, Black will be closer to equality. }
8... Bg7 9. a4
{ Intending to gain some space while prventing ...b5 by Black. If we manage to advance the pawn to a5 we will exert an annoying pressure on the g1-a7 diagonal when our bishop gets to e3. }
9... Rf8 { 9...Ke8  10.a5  . } 10. Bf4 Ke8 11. a5
{ And Black suffers to find useful moves. As they have no squares for their bishop, they cannot connect the rooks and finish the development. The black king would rather like to be on g8. }
