[Round "?"]
[White "11) Hyper Accelerated Dragon"]
[Black "2...g6 3.d4 with 5.c3 y 7.Nb5 #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon. The main advantage of this move order for Black is that is to avoid some sidelines like the Rossolimo @@StartBracket@@3.Bb5 after 2...Nc6@@EndBracket@@. As we are going to play the Open Sicilian, our line will transpose to the standard Accelerated Dragon in most cases. }
3. d4 Bg7
{ A dubious idea, but we have to be careful not to be catched offguard.   3...cxd4  4.Nxd4  Bg7  5.c4  transposing to the Accelerated Dragon. }
4. dxc5
{ Accepting the treat. If Black wants to get the pawn back, they should be quick at the cost of leaving their queen exposed. }
4... Qa5+ 5. c3 Qxc5
{ 5...Nf6  6.b4  Qc7  7.Bd3  consolidating our extra pawn and continuing our development. }
6. Na3
{ The key move. THe knight jumps to b5 or to c4 will be very annoying for Black's queen. }
6... Nf6 { The main move. Black's idea is to castle short quickly. } 7. Nb5
{ Going for the c7-square. } 7... b6
{ The most played move. Black Black puts their pieces in very weird squares to avoid losing material. }
8. b4
{ We continue to take advantage of the fact that Black's queen must control the c7-square to avoid the knight fork and so we can harass it, forcing it to take a very passive position. }
8... Qc6 9. e5 Ne4
{ 9...Ng8  10.Qb3  with a better development and piece placement. Bc4 comes next. }
10. Nfd4 Qb7
{ Black has had to bring his queen this far to avoid a check on c7. } 11. Bd3
{ Exerting pressure quickly on the very loose e4-knight. } 11... a6 12. Qe2
{ The knight has no safe squares to go to. } 12... Nc5
{ After  12...axb5  13.Bxe4  Black's weaknesses are going to start falling soon, especially b5. }
13. bxc5 axb5 14. Be4
{ Exploiting the tactical motif of accumulation of pieces on the long diagonal to exert a lot of pressure there with all our pieces. }
14... Nc6 15. Qf3 { More pressure. } 15... Ra4 { 15...bxc5  16.Nxc6  Ra4  . }
16. Nxc6 bxc5 17. Bd5
{ Forcing Black to go ...e6, leaving the dark squares very weak. } 17... e6 18.
Bg5 { Intending Nd8. } 18... Qa6
{ After  18...Rf8  19.Rd1  exd5  20.Qxd5  the knight is immune to the capture because of the back rank mate and Black can resign. }
19. Nd8 O-O 20. Bb7 Bxb7 21. Nxb7 { White has an extra piece. } *

